<br><br>

<h3>What is the likely impact?</h3>
<p>Potential impacts of the automated house developments are the change in everyday motions undertaken by a person in their day to day lives, examples being  linking an alarm clock to send a signal to start the coffee machine allowing a streamline path in the morning routine. However potential flaws exist as the data collected can provide a deep insight on a personâ€™s everyday activities and privacy concerns may arise from that. The reliance on machines to do everything may also occur through long term usage of automation, once the system breaks or becomes unavailable due to unavoidable reasons people may struggle to return to their normal routine.</p>
<p>Things that will change with this development is the general cost of living for people relying on this technology as household appliances that are able to connect with home automation will be more expensive than those without the integration capabilities to connect with other appliances. </p>



